Shandong Opens Inscribed Tablet Exhibition Hall 
An inscribed tablet exhibition hall recently opened in Qufu, the home
of Confucius.
The garden hall, which is located in the former palaces of Confucius,
covers a floor space of 760 square meters and houses 29 ancient
inscribed tablets dating back to the Han (206 B.C.-220) and Wei
(220-265) dynasties. The tablets reportedly bear the earliest stone
inscriptions in China.
The exhibition also includes 130 ancient inscribed tablets from later
dynasties.
